# Form Component Guidelines

## shadcn/ui Form Components

- Use shadcn/ui form components from `@/components/ui/`
- Import Button, Input, and Label components from their respective files
- Use the `cn()` utility for conditional class names
- Follow shadcn/ui's component API for consistent styling

## Form Security

- Always use `autoComplete="new-password"` for sensitive input fields to prevent browser autofill
- Add unique name attributes to input fields to further prevent autofill (e.g., `name="username_unique"`)
- Add `autoCorrect="off"` and `autoCapitalize="off"` to text inputs where appropriate
- Use `spellCheck="false"` on forms containing sensitive information

## Authentication Forms

- Login form should have empty initial state for email/password fields
- Password visibility toggle should use the Eye/EyeOff icons from lucide-react
- Use proper state management for form fields

## Styling with Tailwind

- Use Tailwind's opacity modifiers (e.g., `bg-white/10`) for semi-transparent elements
- Use `backdrop-blur-xl` for glassmorphism effects
- Follow the project's border radius convention with `rounded-xl`
- Use the project's color variables through Tailwind classes
